xists, kv_incr, kv_decr\", \"status\": \"todo\", \"title\": \"Implement string/scalar operations\"}, {\"notes\": \"Implement bulk operations: kv_mset, kv_mget\", \"status\": \"todo\", \"title\": \"Implement bulk operations\"}, {\"notes\": \"Implement list operations: lpush, rpush, lpop, rpop, lrange\", \"status\": \"todo\", \"title\": \"Implement list operations\"}, {\"notes\": \"Implement set operations: sadd, srem, smembers, scard\", \"status\": \"todo\", \"title\": \"Implement set operations\"}, {\"notes\": \"Implement hash operations: hset, hget, hdel, hgetall\", \"status\": \"todo\", \"title\": \"Implement hash operations\"}, {\"notes\": \"Implement key management: expire, kv_flush, save_to_disk, restore_from_disk\", \"status\": \"todo\", \"title\": \"Implement key management\"}, {\"notes\": \"Implement CommandError exception class\", \"status\": \"todo\", \"title\": \"Implement CommandError exception\"}, {\"notes\": \"Ensure type consistency and expiry handling across all operations\", \"status\": \"todo\", \"title\": \"Ensure type consistency and expiry handling\"}, {\"notes\": \"Test implementation with basic usage scenarios\", \"status\": \"todo\", \"title\": \"Test implementation\"}]}", "kind": "ActionEvent"}
{"id": "e34cb3d2-5ded-4fce-9f3e-661eb7faeec9", "timestamp": "2026-06-28T03:21:24.224116", "source": "environment", "tool_name": "task_tracker", "tool_call_id": "019f0a87869ab16a256c57915b132841", "observation": {"content": [{"cache_prompt": false, "type": "text", "text": "Task list has been updated with 10 item(s)."}], "is_error": false, "command": "plan", "task_list": [{"title": "Implement QueueServer class", "notes": "Implement QueueServer class with type-tagged key namespace", "status": "in_progress"}, {"title": "Implement string/scalar operations", "notes": "Implement string/scalar operations: kv_set, kv_get, kv_delete, kv_exists, kv_incr, kv_decr", "status": "todo"}, {"title": "Implement bulk operations", "notes": "Implement bulk operations: kv_mset, kv_mget", "status": "todo"}, {"title": "Implement list operations", "notes": "Implement list operations: lpush, rpush, lpop, rpop, lrange", "status": "todo"}, {"title": "Implement set operations", "notes": "Implement set operations: sadd, srem, smembers, scard", "status": "todo"}, {"title": "Implement hash operations", "notes": "Implement hash operations: hset, hget, hdel, hgetall", "status": "todo"}, {"title": "Implement key management", "notes": "Implement key management: expire, kv_flush, save_to_disk, restore_from_disk", "status": "todo"}, {"title": "Implement CommandError exception", "notes": "Implement CommandError exception class", "status": "todo"}, {"title": "Ensure type consistency and expiry handling", "notes": "Ensure type consistency and expiry handling across all operations", "status": "todo"}, {"title": "Test implementation", "notes": "Test implementation with basic usage scenarios", "status": "todo"}], "kind": "TaskTrackerObservation"}, "action_id": "44e0e47a-fc87-4082-aa07-bd37ddfc57cc", "kind": "ObservationEvent"}
{"id": "8543e132-1121-4292-b126-363db49d9253", "timestamp": "2026-06-28T03:23:30.012242", "source": "agent", "thought": [{"cache_prompt": false, "type": "text", "text": "\n\n"}], "reasoning_content": null, "thinking_blocks": [], "responses_reasoning_item": null, "action": {"command": "create", "path": "G:\\research\\01_agents\\swe-e2e\\Bmk-dev\\runs\\minikv-realrepo-submit\\solution-openhands-qwen-001\\minikv.py", "file_text": "\"\"\"\nMiniKV - In-memory data structure store library.\n\nProvides QueueServer class that stores strings/numbers, lists, sets, and hashes\nin a single key namespace with type-tagged state.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport pickle\nimport time\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\nclass CommandError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Raised for type mismatches and invalid operations.\"\"\"\n    pass\n\n\nclass QueueServer:\n    \"\"\"\n    In-memory key-value store supporting strings, lists, sets, and hashes.\n    \n    Every key has one canonical type at a time, with type detection based on\n    the value stored: dict->HASH, list->QUEUE, set->SET, others->KV.\n    \"\"\"\n    \n    # Type tags\n    KV = \"KV\"\n    QUEUE = \"QUEUE\"\n    SET = \"SET\"\n    HASH = \"HASH\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, use_gevent: bool = False):\n        \"\"\"Create a new data store instance.\n        \n        Args:\n            use_gevent: Ignored for this task; always pass False.\n        \"\"\"\n        # Main storage: key -> (value, type_tag, expiry_time_or_None)\n        self._store: dict[str, tuple[Any, str, float | None]] = {}\n        self._use_gevent = use_gevent\n    \n    def _get_entry(self, key: str) -> tuple[Any, str, float | None] | None:\n        \"\"\"Get store entry if exists and not expired, applying lazy expiration.\"\"\"\n        if key not in self._store:\n            return None\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = self._store[key]\n        \n        # Lazy expiration check\n        if expiry is not None and time.time() > expiry:\n            del self._store[key]\n            return None\n        \n        return (value, type_tag, expiry)\n    \n    def _delete_expired(self, key: str) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Delete key if expired. Returns True if deleted.\"\"\"\n        if key not in self._store:\n            return False\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = self._store[key]\n        if expiry is not None and time.time() > expiry:\n            del self._store[key]\n            return True\n        return False\n    \n    def _detect_type(self, value: Any) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Detect type tag from value.\"\"\"\n        if isinstance(value, dict):\n            return self.HASH\n        elif isinstance(value, list):\n            return self.QUEUE\n        elif isinstance(value, set):\n            return self.SET\n        else:\n            return self.KV\n    \n    # ==================== String and Scalar Operations ====================\n    \n    def kv_set(self, key: str, value: Any) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Store a value.\n        \n        Type is auto-detected: dict->HASH, list->QUEUE, set->SET, others->KV.\n        Overwrites any previous value, type, and expiry.\n        \n        Returns:\n            1\n        \"\"\"\n        type_tag = self._detect_type(value)\n        self._store[key] = (value, type_tag, None)\n        return 1\n    \n    def kv_get(self, key: str) -> Any | None:\n        \"\"\"Return the stored value, or None if key doesn't exist or expired.\"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        if entry is None:\n            return None\n        value, _, _ = entry\n        return value\n    \n    def kv_delete(self, key: str) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Remove the key, including type and expiry metadata.\n        \n        Returns:\n            1 if deleted, 0 if not found.\n        \"\"\"\n        if self._delete_expired(key):\n            return 1\n        if key in self._store:\n            del self._store[key]\n            return 1\n        return 0\n    \n    def kv_exists(self, key: str) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Return 1 if key exists and not expired, otherwise 0.\"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        return 1 if entry is not None else 0\n    \n    def kv_incr(self, key: str) -> int | float:\n        \"\"\"Increment a numeric KV value by 1.\n        \n        If key doesn't exist, creates it at 0 then increments to 1.\n        Raises CommandError on non-numeric values or wrong types.\n        \n        Returns:\n            The new value.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            # Create new key starting at 0, then increment to 1\n            self._store[key] = (1, self.KV, None)\n            return 1\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.KV:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        if not isinstance(value, (int, float)):\n            raise CommandError(\"ERR value is not an integer or float\")\n        \n        new_value = value + 1\n        self._store[key] = (new_value, self.KV, expiry)\n        return new_value\n    \n    def kv_decr(self, key: str) -> int | float:\n        \"\"\"Decrement a numeric KV value by 1.\n        \n        If key doesn't exist, creates it at 0 then decrements to -1.\n        Raises CommandError on non-numeric values or wrong types.\n        \n        Returns:\n            The new value.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            # Create new key starting at 0, then decrement to -1\n            self._store[key] = (-1, self.KV, None)\n            return -1\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.KV:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        if not isinstance(value, (int, float)):\n            raise CommandError(\"ERR value is not an integer or float\")\n        \n        new_value = value - 1\n        self._store[key] = (new_value, self.KV, expiry)\n        return new_value\n    \n    # ==================== Bulk Operations ====================\n    \n    def kv_mset(self, __data: dict | None = None, **kwargs) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Set multiple keys from a dict and/or keyword arguments.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Count of keys set.\n        \"\"\"\n        count = 0\n        \n        if __data is not None:\n            for key, value in __data.items():\n                self.kv_set(key, value)\n                count += 1\n        \n        for key, value in kwargs.items():\n            self.kv_set(key, value)\n            count += 1\n        \n        return count\n    \n    def kv_mget(self, *keys) -> list:\n        \"\"\"Return a list of direct-read values in the same order as requested keys.\n        \n        Missing or expired keys appear as None.\n        \"\"\"\n        return [self.kv_get(key) for key in keys]\n    \n    # ==================== List Operations ====================\n    \n    def lpush(self, key: str, *values) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Prepend values to the head of a list.\n        \n        Creates the list if it doesn't exist. Values applied in argument order.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Number of values pushed.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            # Create new list\n            new_list = list(values)\n            self._store[key] = (new_list, self.QUEUE, None)\n            return len(values)\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.QUEUE:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        # Prepend in argument order (so lpush(\"q\", \"a\", \"b\") gives [\"b\", \"a\", ...])\n        for v in reversed(values):\n            value.insert(0, v)\n        \n        self._store[key] = (value, self.QUEUE, expiry)\n        return len(value)\n    \n    def rpush(self, key: str, *values) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Append values to the tail.\n        \n        Creates the list if it doesn't exist.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Number of values pushed.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            # Create new list\n            new_list = list(values)\n            self._store[key] = (new_list, self.QUEUE, None)\n            return len(values)\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.QUEUE:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        value.extend(values)\n        self._store[key] = (value, self.QUEUE, expiry)\n        return len(value)\n    \n    def lpop(self, key: str) -> Any | None:\n        \"\"\"Remove and return the first element.\n        \n        Returns:\n            First element, or None if list is empty or missing.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            return None\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.QUEUE:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        if not value:\n            return None\n        \n        result = value.pop(0)\n        self._store[key] = (value, self.QUEUE, expiry)\n        return result\n    \n    def rpop(self, key: str) -> Any | None:\n        \"\"\"Remove and return the last element.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Last element, or None if list is empty or missing.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            return None\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.QUEUE:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        if not value:\n            return None\n        \n        result = value.pop()\n        self._store[key] = (value, self.QUEUE, expiry)\n        return result\n    \n    def lrange(self, key: str, start: int, end: int | None = None) -> list:\n        \"\"\"Return a list slice using Python slice semantics [start:end].\n        \n        Args:\n            key: The list key\n            start: Start index\n            end: End index (None means \"to the end\")\n        \n        Returns:\n            List slice, or [] for missing keys.\n        \n        Raises:\n            CommandError: On non-list keys.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            return []\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.QUEUE:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        # Python slice semantics\n        return list(value[start:end])\n    \n    # ==================== Set Operations ====================\n    \n    def sadd(self, key: str, *members) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Add members to a set.\n        \n        Creates the set if it doesn't exist.\n        \n        Returns:\n            New cardinality.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            # Create new set\n            new_set = set(members)\n            self._store[key] = (new_set, self.SET, None)\n            return len(new_set)\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.SET:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        value.update(members)\n        self._store[key] = (value, self.SET, expiry)\n        return len(value)\n    \n    def srem(self, key: str, *members) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Remove members from set.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Count of members actually removed.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            return 0\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.SET:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        removed = 0\n        for member in members:\n            if member in value:\n                value.remove(member)\n                removed += 1\n        \n        self._store[key] = (value, self.SET, expiry)\n        return removed\n    \n    def smembers(self, key: str) -> set:\n        \"\"\"Return the internal set object.\n        \n        If key doesn't exist, creates an empty set first.\n        \n        Returns:\n            The set object.\n        \n        Raises:\n            CommandError: On non-set keys.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            # Create empty set\n            new_set = set()\n            self._store[key] = (new_set, self.SET, None)\n            return new_set\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.SET:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        return value\n    \n    def scard(self, key: str) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Return the cardinality.\n        \n        If key doesn't exist, creates an empty set and returns 0.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Number of members in set.\n        \n        Raises:\n            CommandError: On non-set keys.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            # Create empty set\n            new_set = set()\n            self._store[key] = (new_set, self.SET, None)\n            return 0\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.SET:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        return len(value)\n    \n    # ==================== Hash Operations ====================\n    \n    def hset(self, key: str, field: str, value: Any) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Set a field in hash.\n        \n        Creates the hash if it doesn't exist.\n        \n        Returns:\n            1\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            # Create new hash\n            new_dict = {field: value}\n            self._store[key] = (new_dict, self.HASH, None)\n            return 1\n        \n        value_store, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.HASH:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        value_store[field] = value\n        self._store[key] = (value_store, self.HASH, expiry)\n        return 1\n    \n    def hget(self, key: str, field: str) -> Any | None:\n        \"\"\"Return the field value.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Field value, or None if hash or field doesn't exist.\n        \n        Raises:\n            CommandError: On non-hash keys.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            return None\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.HASH:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        return value.get(field)\n    \n    def hdel(self, key: str, field: str) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Delete a field from hash.\n        \n        Returns:\n            1 if deleted, 0 if not found.\n        \n        Raises:\n            CommandError: On non-hash keys.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            return 0\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.HASH:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        if field in value:\n            del value[field]\n            self._store[key] = (value, self.HASH, expiry)\n            return 1\n        \n        return 0\n    \n    def hgetall(self, key: str) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Return the internal dict object.\n        \n        If key doesn't exist, creates an empty hash first.\n        \n        Returns:\n            The dict object.\n        \n        Raises:\n            CommandError: On non-hash keys.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            # Create empty hash\n            new_dict = {}\n            self._store[key] = (new_dict, self.HASH, None)\n            return new_dict\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.HASH:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        return value\n    \n    # ==================== Key Management ====================\n    \n    def expire(self, key: str, nseconds: int) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Set a timeout in seconds for a live key.\n        \n        Calling for a missing key is a no-op.\n        \n        Returns:\n            None\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            return None\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        self._store[key] = (value, type_tag, time.time() + nseconds)\n        return None\n    \n    def kv_flush(self) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Remove all live keys and metadata.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Number of live keys removed.\n        \"\"\"\n        count = 0\n        now = time.time()\n        keys_to_delete = []\n        \n        for key, (value, type_tag, expiry) in self._store.items():\n            if expiry is None or expiry > now:\n                keys_to_delete.append(key)\n        \n        for key in keys_to_delete:\n            del self._store[key]\n            count += 1\n        \n        return count\n    \n    def save_to_disk(self, filename: str) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Persist the entire database state to a file using pickle.\n        \n        Returns:\n            True\n        \"\"\"\n        # Clean up expired keys before saving\n        now = time.time()\n        live_store = {}\n        for key, (value, type_tag, expiry) in self._store.items():\n            if expiry is None or expiry > now:\n                live_store[key] = (value, type_tag, expiry)\n        \n        with open(filename, 'wb') as f:\n            pickle.dump(live_store, f)\n        return True\n    \n    def restore_from_disk(self, filename: str) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Restore database state from a pickle file.\n        \n        Returns:\n            True if restored, False if file doesn't exist.\n        \"\"\"\n        import os\n        if not os.path.exists(filename):\n            return False\n        \n        with open(filename, 'rb') as f:\n            self._store = pickle.load(f)\n        return True", "old_str": null, "new_str": null, "insert_line": null, "view_range": null, "kind": "FileEditorAction"}, "tool_name": "file_editor", "tool_call_id": "019f0a89727a1895d34081244b10c941", "tool_call": {"id": "019f0a89727a1895d34081244b10c941", "responses_item_id": null, "name": "file_editor", "arguments": "{\"command\": \"create\", \"file_text\": \"\\\"\\\"\\\"\\nMiniKV - In-memory data structure store library.\\n\\nProvides QueueServer class that stores strings/numbers, lists, sets, and hashes\\nin a single key namespace with type-tagged state.\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n\\nimport pickle\\nimport time\\nfrom typing import Any\\n\\n\\nclass CommandError(Exception):\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"Raised for type mismatches and invalid operations.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    pass\\n\\n\\nclass QueueServer:\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    In-memory key-value store supporting strings, lists, sets, and hashes.\\n    \\n    Every key has one canonical type at a time, with type detection based on\\n    the value stored: dict->HASH, list->QUEUE, set->SET, others->KV.\\n    \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n    \\n    # Type tags\\n    KV = \\\"KV\\\"\\n    QUEUE = \\\"QUEUE\\\"\\n    SET = \\\"SET\\\"\\n    HASH = \\\"HASH\\\"\\n    \\n    def __init__(self, use_gevent: bool = False):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Create a new data store instance.\\n        \\n        Args:\\n            use_gevent: Ignored for this task; always pass False.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # Main storage: key -> (value, type_tag, expiry_time_or_None)\\n        self._store: dict[str, tuple[Any, str, float | None]] = {}\\n        self._use_gevent = use_gevent\\n    \\n    def _get_entry(self, key: str) -> tuple[Any, str, float | None] | None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Get store entry if exists and not expired, applying lazy expiration.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if key not in self._store:\\n            return None\\n        \\n        value, type_tag, expiry = self._store[key]\\n        \\n        # Lazy expiration check\\n        if expiry is not None and time.time() > expiry:\\n            del self._store[key]\\n            return None\\n        \\n        return (value, type_tag, expiry)\\n    \\n    def _delete_expired(self, key: str) -> bool:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Delete key if expired. Returns True if deleted.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if key not in self._store:\\n            return False\\n        \\n        value, type_tag, expiry = self._store[key]\\n        if expiry is not None and time.time() > expiry:\\n            del self._store[key]\\n            return True\\n        return False\\n    \\n    def _detect_type(self, value: Any) -> str:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Detect type tag from value.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if isinstance(value, dict):\\n            return self.HASH\\n        elif isinstance(value, list):\\n            return self.QUEUE\\n        elif isinstance(value, set):\\n            return self.SET\\n        else:\\n            return self.KV\\n    \\n    # ==================== String and Scalar Operations ====================\\n    \\n    def kv_set(self, key: str, value: Any) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Store a value.\\n        \\n        Type is auto-detected: dict->HASH, list->QUEUE, set->SET, others->KV.\\n        Overwrites any previous value, type, and expiry.\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            1\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        type_tag = self._detect_type(value)\\n        self._store[key] = (value, type_tag, None)\\n        return 1\\n    \\n    def kv_get(self, key: str) -> Any | None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Return the stored value, or None if key doesn't exist or expired.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\\n        if entry is None:\\n            return None\\n        value, _, _ = entry\\n        return value\\n    \\n    def kv_delete(self, key: str) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Remove the key, including type and expiry metadata.\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            1 if deleted, 0 if not found.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        if self._delete_expired(key):\\n            return 1\\n        if key in self._store:\\n            del self._store[key]\\n            return 1\\n        return 0\\n    \\n    def kv_exists(self, key: str) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Return 1 if key exists and not expired, otherwise 0.\\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\\n        return 1 if entry is not None else 0\\n    \\n    def kv_incr(self, key: str) -> int | float:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Increment a numeric KV value by 1.\\n        \\n        If key doesn't exist, creates it at 0 then increments to 1.\\n        Raises CommandError on non-numeric values or wrong types.\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            The new value.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\\n        \\n        if entry is None:\\n            # Create new key starting at 0, then increment to 1\\n            self._store[key] = (1, self.KV, None)\\n            return 1\\n        \\n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\\n        \\n        if type_tag != self.KV:\\n            raise CommandError(f\\\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\\\")\\n        \\n        if not isinstance(value, (int, float)):\\n            raise CommandError(\\\"ERR value is not an integer or float\\\")\\n        \\n        new_value = value + 1\\n        self._store[key] = (new_value, self.KV, expiry)\\n        return new_value\\n    \\n    def kv_decr(self, key: str) -> int | float:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Decrement a numeric KV value by 1.\\n        \\n        If key doesn't exist, creates it at 0 then decrements to -1.\\n        Raises CommandError on non-numeric values or wrong types.\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            The new value.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\\n        \\n        if entry is None:\\n            # Create new key starting at 0, then decrement to -1\\n            self._store[key] = (-1, self.KV, None)\\n            return -1\\n        \\n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\\n        \\n        if type_tag != self.KV:\\n            raise CommandError(f\\\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\\\")\\n        \\n        if not isinstance(value, (int, float)):\\n            raise CommandError(\\\"ERR value is not an integer or float\\\")\\n        \\n        new_value = value - 1\\n        self._store[key] = (new_value, self.KV, expiry)\\n        return new_value\\n    \\n    # ==================== Bulk Operations ====================\\n    \\n    def kv_mset(self, __data: dict | None = None, **kwargs) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Set multiple keys from a dict and/or keyword arguments.\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            Count of keys set.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        count = 0\\n        \\n        if __data is not None:\\n            for key, value in __data.items():\\n                self.kv_set(key, value)\\n                count += 1\\n        \\n        for key, value in kwargs.items():\\n            self.kv_set(key, value)\\n            count += 1\\n        \\n        return count\\n    \\n    def kv_mget(self, *keys) -> list:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Return a list of direct-read values in the same order as requested keys.\\n        \\n        Missing or expired keys appear as None.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        return [self.kv_get(key) for key in keys]\\n    \\n    # ==================== List Operations ====================\\n    \\n    def lpush(self, key: str, *values) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Prepend values to the head of a list.\\n        \\n        Creates the list if it doesn't exist. Values applied in argument order.\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            Number of values pushed.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\\n        \\n        if entry is None:\\n            # Create new list\\n            new_list = list(values)\\n            self._store[key] = (new_list, self.QUEUE, None)\\n            return len(values)\\n        \\n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\\n        \\n        if type_tag != self.QUEUE:\\n            raise CommandError(f\\\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\\\")\\n        \\n        # Prepend in argument order (so lpush(\\\"q\\\", \\\"a\\\", \\\"b\\\") gives [\\\"b\\\", \\\"a\\\", ...])\\n        for v in reversed(values):\\n            value.insert(0, v)\\n        \\n        self._store[key] = (value, self.QUEUE, expiry)\\n        return len(value)\\n    \\n    def rpush(self, key: str, *values) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Append values to the tail.\\n        \\n        Creates the list if it doesn't exist.\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            Number of values pushed.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\\n        \\n        if entry is None:\\n            # Create new list\\n            new_list = list(values)\\n            self._store[key] = (new_list, self.QUEUE, None)\\n            return len(values)\\n        \\n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\\n        \\n        if type_tag != self.QUEUE:\\n            raise CommandError(f\\\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\\\")\\n        \\n        value.extend(values)\\n        self._store[key] = (value, self.QUEUE, expiry)\\n        return len(value)\\n    \\n    def lpop(self, key: str) -> Any | None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Remove and return the first element.\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            First element, or None if list is empty or missing.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\\n        \\n        if entry is None:\\n            return None\\n        \\n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\\n        \\n        if type_tag != self.QUEUE:\\n            raise CommandError(f\\\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\\\")\\n        \\n        if not value:\\n            return None\\n        \\n        result = value.pop(0)\\n        self._store[key] = (value, self.QUEUE, expiry)\\n        return result\\n    \\n    def rpop(self, key: str) -> Any | None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Remove and return the last element.\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            Last element, or None if list is empty or missing.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\\n        \\n        if entry is None:\\n            return None\\n        \\n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\\n        \\n        if type_tag != self.QUEUE:\\n            raise CommandError(f\\\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\\\")\\n        \\n        if not value:\\n            return None\\n        \\n        result = value.pop()\\n        self._store[key] = (value, self.QUEUE, expiry)\\n        return result\\n    \\n    def lrange(self, key: str, start: int, end: int | None = None) -> list:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Return a list slice using Python slice semantics [start:end].\\n        \\n        Args:\\n            key: The list key\\n            start: Start index\\n            end: End index (None means \\\"to the end\\\")\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            List slice, or [] for missing keys.\\n        \\n        Raises:\\n            CommandError: On non-list keys.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\\n        \\n        if entry is None:\\n            return []\\n        \\n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\\n        \\n        if type_tag != self.QUEUE:\\n            raise CommandError(f\\\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\\\")\\n        \\n        # Python slice semantics\\n        return list(value[start:end])\\n    \\n    # ==================== Set Operations ====================\\n    \\n    def sadd(self, key: str, *members) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Add members to a set.\\n        \\n        Creates the set if it doesn't exist.\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            New cardinality.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\\n        \\n        if entry is None:\\n            # Create new set\\n            new_set = set(members)\\n            self._store[key] = (new_set, self.SET, None)\\n            return len(new_set)\\n        \\n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\\n        \\n        if type_tag != self.SET:\\n            raise CommandError(f\\\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\\\")\\n        \\n        value.update(members)\\n        self._store[key] = (value, self.SET, expiry)\\n        return len(value)\\n    \\n    def srem(self, key: str, *members) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Remove members from set.\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            Count of members actually removed.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\\n        \\n        if entry is None:\\n            return 0\\n        \\n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\\n        \\n        if type_tag != self.SET:\\n            raise CommandError(f\\\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\\\")\\n        \\n        removed = 0\\n        for member in members:\\n            if member in value:\\n                value.remove(member)\\n                removed += 1\\n        \\n        self._store[key] = (value, self.SET, expiry)\\n        return removed\\n    \\n    def smembers(self, key: str) -> set:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Return the internal set object.\\n        \\n        If key doesn't exist, creates an empty set first.\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            The set object.\\n        \\n        Raises:\\n            CommandError: On non-set keys.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\\n        \\n        if entry is None:\\n            # Create empty set\\n            new_set = set()\\n            self._store[key] = (new_set, self.SET, None)\\n            return new_set\\n        \\n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\\n        \\n        if type_tag != self.SET:\\n            raise CommandError(f\\\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\\\")\\n        \\n        return value\\n    \\n    def scard(self, key: str) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Return the cardinality.\\n        \\n        If key doesn't exist, creates an empty set and returns 0.\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            Number of members in set.\\n        \\n        Raises:\\n            CommandError: On non-set keys.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\\n        \\n        if entry is None:\\n            # Create empty set\\n            new_set = set()\\n            self._store[key] = (new_set, self.SET, None)\\n            return 0\\n        \\n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\\n        \\n        if type_tag != self.SET:\\n            raise CommandError(f\\\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\\\")\\n        \\n        return len(value)\\n    \\n    # ==================== Hash Operations ====================\\n    \\n    def hset(self, key: str, field: str, value: Any) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Set a field in hash.\\n        \\n        Creates the hash if it doesn't exist.\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            1\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\\n        \\n        if entry is None:\\n            # Create new hash\\n            new_dict = {field: value}\\n            self._store[key] = (new_dict, self.HASH, None)\\n            return 1\\n        \\n        value_store, type_tag, expiry = entry\\n        \\n        if type_tag != self.HASH:\\n            raise CommandError(f\\\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\\\")\\n        \\n        value_store[field] = value\\n        self._store[key] = (value_store, self.HASH, expiry)\\n        return 1\\n    \\n    def hget(self, key: str, field: str) -> Any | None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Return the field value.\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            Field value, or None if hash or field doesn't exist.\\n        \\n        Raises:\\n            CommandError: On non-hash keys.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\\n        \\n        if entry is None:\\n            return None\\n        \\n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\\n        \\n        if type_tag != self.HASH:\\n            raise CommandError(f\\\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\\\")\\n        \\n        return value.get(field)\\n    \\n    def hdel(self, key: str, field: str) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Delete a field from hash.\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            1 if deleted, 0 if not found.\\n        \\n        Raises:\\n            CommandError: On non-hash keys.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\\n        \\n        if entry is None:\\n            return 0\\n        \\n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\\n        \\n        if type_tag != self.HASH:\\n            raise CommandError(f\\\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\\\")\\n        \\n        if field in value:\\n            del value[field]\\n            self._store[key] = (value, self.HASH, expiry)\\n            return 1\\n        \\n        return 0\\n    \\n    def hgetall(self, key: str) -> dict:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Return the internal dict object.\\n        \\n        If key doesn't exist, creates an empty hash first.\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            The dict object.\\n        \\n        Raises:\\n            CommandError: On non-hash keys.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\\n        \\n        if entry is None:\\n            # Create empty hash\\n            new_dict = {}\\n            self._store[key] = (new_dict, self.HASH, None)\\n            return new_dict\\n        \\n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\\n        \\n        if type_tag != self.HASH:\\n            raise CommandError(f\\\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\\\")\\n        \\n        return value\\n    \\n    # ==================== Key Management ====================\\n    \\n    def expire(self, key: str, nseconds: int) -> None:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Set a timeout in seconds for a live key.\\n        \\n        Calling for a missing key is a no-op.\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            None\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\\n        \\n        if entry is None:\\n            return None\\n        \\n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\\n        self._store[key] = (value, type_tag, time.time() + nseconds)\\n        return None\\n    \\n    def kv_flush(self) -> int:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Remove all live keys and metadata.\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            Number of live keys removed.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        count = 0\\n        now = time.time()\\n        keys_to_delete = []\\n        \\n        for key, (value, type_tag, expiry) in self._store.items():\\n            if expiry is None or expiry > now:\\n                keys_to_delete.append(key)\\n        \\n        for key in keys_to_delete:\\n            del self._store[key]\\n            count += 1\\n        \\n        return count\\n    \\n    def save_to_disk(self, filename: str) -> bool:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Persist the entire database state to a file using pickle.\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            True\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        # Clean up expired keys before saving\\n        now = time.time()\\n        live_store = {}\\n        for key, (value, type_tag, expiry) in self._store.items():\\n            if expiry is None or expiry > now:\\n                live_store[key] = (value, type_tag, expiry)\\n        \\n        with open(filename, 'wb') as f:\\n            pickle.dump(live_store, f)\\n        return True\\n    \\n    def restore_from_disk(self, filename: str) -> bool:\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Restore database state from a pickle file.\\n        \\n        Returns:\\n            True if restored, False if file doesn't exist.\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        import os\\n        if not os.path.exists(filename):\\n            return False\\n        \\n        with open(filename, 'rb') as f:\\n            self._store = pickle.load(f)\\n        return True\", \"path\": \"G:\\\\research\\\\01_agents\\\\swe-e2e\\\\Bmk-dev\\\\runs\\\\minikv-realrepo-submit\\\\solution-openhands-qwen-001\\\\minikv.py\", \"security_risk\": \"LOW\", \"summary\": \"Create MiniKV implementation\"}", "origin": "completion"}, "llm_response_id": "019f0a8789f49d5b4328f7d97cde6d97", "security_risk": "LOW", "critic_result": null, "summary": "Create MiniKV implementation", "kind": "ActionEvent"}
{"id": "ffb329fb-d69e-4081-adc7-9e20e7b1822f", "timestamp": "2026-06-28T03:23:30.225799", "source": "environment", "tool_name": "file_editor", "tool_call_id": "019f0a89727a1895d34081244b10c941", "observation": {"content": [{"cache_prompt": false, "type": "text", "text": "File created successfully at: G:\\research\\01_agents\\swe-e2e\\Bmk-dev\\runs\\minikv-realrepo-submit\\solution-openhands-qwen-001\\minikv.py"}], "is_error": false, "command": "create", "path": "G:\\research\\01_agents\\swe-e2e\\Bmk-dev\\runs\\minikv-realrepo-submit\\solution-openhands-qwen-001\\minikv.py", "prev_exist": false, "old_content": null, "new_content": "\"\"\"\nMiniKV - In-memory data structure store library.\n\nProvides QueueServer class that stores strings/numbers, lists, sets, and hashes\nin a single key namespace with type-tagged state.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport pickle\nimport time\nfrom typing import Any\n\n\nclass CommandError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Raised for type mismatches and invalid operations.\"\"\"\n    pass\n\n\nclass QueueServer:\n    \"\"\"\n    In-memory key-value store supporting strings, lists, sets, and hashes.\n    \n    Every key has one canonical type at a time, with type detection based on\n    the value stored: dict->HASH, list->QUEUE, set->SET, others->KV.\n    \"\"\"\n    \n    # Type tags\n    KV = \"KV\"\n    QUEUE = \"QUEUE\"\n    SET = \"SET\"\n    HASH = \"HASH\"\n    \n    def __init__(self, use_gevent: bool = False):\n        \"\"\"Create a new data store instance.\n        \n        Args:\n            use_gevent: Ignored for this task; always pass False.\n        \"\"\"\n        # Main storage: key -> (value, type_tag, expiry_time_or_None)\n        self._store: dict[str, tuple[Any, str, float | None]] = {}\n        self._use_gevent = use_gevent\n    \n    def _get_entry(self, key: str) -> tuple[Any, str, float | None] | None:\n        \"\"\"Get store entry if exists and not expired, applying lazy expiration.\"\"\"\n        if key not in self._store:\n            return None\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = self._store[key]\n        \n        # Lazy expiration check\n        if expiry is not None and time.time() > expiry:\n            del self._store[key]\n            return None\n        \n        return (value, type_tag, expiry)\n    \n    def _delete_expired(self, key: str) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Delete key if expired. Returns True if deleted.\"\"\"\n        if key not in self._store:\n            return False\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = self._store[key]\n        if expiry is not None and time.time() > expiry:\n            del self._store[key]\n            return True\n        return False\n    \n    def _detect_type(self, value: Any) -> str:\n        \"\"\"Detect type tag from value.\"\"\"\n        if isinstance(value, dict):\n            return self.HASH\n        elif isinstance(value, list):\n            return self.QUEUE\n        elif isinstance(value, set):\n            return self.SET\n        else:\n            return self.KV\n    \n    # ==================== String and Scalar Operations ====================\n    \n    def kv_set(self, key: str, value: Any) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Store a value.\n        \n        Type is auto-detected: dict->HASH, list->QUEUE, set->SET, others->KV.\n        Overwrites any previous value, type, and expiry.\n        \n        Returns:\n            1\n        \"\"\"\n        type_tag = self._detect_type(value)\n        self._store[key] = (value, type_tag, None)\n        return 1\n    \n    def kv_get(self, key: str) -> Any | None:\n        \"\"\"Return the stored value, or None if key doesn't exist or expired.\"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        if entry is None:\n            return None\n        value, _, _ = entry\n        return value\n    \n    def kv_delete(self, key: str) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Remove the key, including type and expiry metadata.\n        \n        Returns:\n            1 if deleted, 0 if not found.\n        \"\"\"\n        if self._delete_expired(key):\n            return 1\n        if key in self._store:\n            del self._store[key]\n            return 1\n        return 0\n    \n    def kv_exists(self, key: str) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Return 1 if key exists and not expired, otherwise 0.\"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        return 1 if entry is not None else 0\n    \n    def kv_incr(self, key: str) -> int | float:\n        \"\"\"Increment a numeric KV value by 1.\n        \n        If key doesn't exist, creates it at 0 then increments to 1.\n        Raises CommandError on non-numeric values or wrong types.\n        \n        Returns:\n            The new value.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            # Create new key starting at 0, then increment to 1\n            self._store[key] = (1, self.KV, None)\n            return 1\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.KV:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        if not isinstance(value, (int, float)):\n            raise CommandError(\"ERR value is not an integer or float\")\n        \n        new_value = value + 1\n        self._store[key] = (new_value, self.KV, expiry)\n        return new_value\n    \n    def kv_decr(self, key: str) -> int | float:\n        \"\"\"Decrement a numeric KV value by 1.\n        \n        If key doesn't exist, creates it at 0 then decrements to -1.\n        Raises CommandError on non-numeric values or wrong types.\n        \n        Returns:\n            The new value.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            # Create new key starting at 0, then decrement to -1\n            self._store[key] = (-1, self.KV, None)\n            return -1\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.KV:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        if not isinstance(value, (int, float)):\n            raise CommandError(\"ERR value is not an integer or float\")\n        \n        new_value = value - 1\n        self._store[key] = (new_value, self.KV, expiry)\n        return new_value\n    \n    # ==================== Bulk Operations ====================\n    \n    def kv_mset(self, __data: dict | None = None, **kwargs) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Set multiple keys from a dict and/or keyword arguments.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Count of keys set.\n        \"\"\"\n        count = 0\n        \n        if __data is not None:\n            for key, value in __data.items():\n                self.kv_set(key, value)\n                count += 1\n        \n        for key, value in kwargs.items():\n            self.kv_set(key, value)\n            count += 1\n        \n        return count\n    \n    def kv_mget(self, *keys) -> list:\n        \"\"\"Return a list of direct-read values in the same order as requested keys.\n        \n        Missing or expired keys appear as None.\n        \"\"\"\n        return [self.kv_get(key) for key in keys]\n    \n    # ==================== List Operations ====================\n    \n    def lpush(self, key: str, *values) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Prepend values to the head of a list.\n        \n        Creates the list if it doesn't exist. Values applied in argument order.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Number of values pushed.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            # Create new list\n            new_list = list(values)\n            self._store[key] = (new_list, self.QUEUE, None)\n            return len(values)\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.QUEUE:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        # Prepend in argument order (so lpush(\"q\", \"a\", \"b\") gives [\"b\", \"a\", ...])\n        for v in reversed(values):\n            value.insert(0, v)\n        \n        self._store[key] = (value, self.QUEUE, expiry)\n        return len(value)\n    \n    def rpush(self, key: str, *values) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Append values to the tail.\n        \n        Creates the list if it doesn't exist.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Number of values pushed.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            # Create new list\n            new_list = list(values)\n            self._store[key] = (new_list, self.QUEUE, None)\n            return len(values)\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.QUEUE:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        value.extend(values)\n        self._store[key] = (value, self.QUEUE, expiry)\n        return len(value)\n    \n    def lpop(self, key: str) -> Any | None:\n        \"\"\"Remove and return the first element.\n        \n        Returns:\n            First element, or None if list is empty or missing.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            return None\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.QUEUE:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        if not value:\n            return None\n        \n        result = value.pop(0)\n        self._store[key] = (value, self.QUEUE, expiry)\n        return result\n    \n    def rpop(self, key: str) -> Any | None:\n        \"\"\"Remove and return the last element.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Last element, or None if list is empty or missing.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            return None\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.QUEUE:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        if not value:\n            return None\n        \n        result = value.pop()\n        self._store[key] = (value, self.QUEUE, expiry)\n        return result\n    \n    def lrange(self, key: str, start: int, end: int | None = None) -> list:\n        \"\"\"Return a list slice using Python slice semantics [start:end].\n        \n        Args:\n            key: The list key\n            start: Start index\n            end: End index (None means \"to the end\")\n        \n        Returns:\n            List slice, or [] for missing keys.\n        \n        Raises:\n            CommandError: On non-list keys.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            return []\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.QUEUE:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        # Python slice semantics\n        return list(value[start:end])\n    \n    # ==================== Set Operations ====================\n    \n    def sadd(self, key: str, *members) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Add members to a set.\n        \n        Creates the set if it doesn't exist.\n        \n        Returns:\n            New cardinality.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            # Create new set\n            new_set = set(members)\n            self._store[key] = (new_set, self.SET, None)\n            return len(new_set)\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.SET:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        value.update(members)\n        self._store[key] = (value, self.SET, expiry)\n        return len(value)\n    \n    def srem(self, key: str, *members) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Remove members from set.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Count of members actually removed.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            return 0\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.SET:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        removed = 0\n        for member in members:\n            if member in value:\n                value.remove(member)\n                removed += 1\n        \n        self._store[key] = (value, self.SET, expiry)\n        return removed\n    \n    def smembers(self, key: str) -> set:\n        \"\"\"Return the internal set object.\n        \n        If key doesn't exist, creates an empty set first.\n        \n        Returns:\n            The set object.\n        \n        Raises:\n            CommandError: On non-set keys.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            # Create empty set\n            new_set = set()\n            self._store[key] = (new_set, self.SET, None)\n            return new_set\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.SET:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        return value\n    \n    def scard(self, key: str) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Return the cardinality.\n        \n        If key doesn't exist, creates an empty set and returns 0.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Number of members in set.\n        \n        Raises:\n            CommandError: On non-set keys.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            # Create empty set\n            new_set = set()\n            self._store[key] = (new_set, self.SET, None)\n            return 0\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.SET:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        return len(value)\n    \n    # ==================== Hash Operations ====================\n    \n    def hset(self, key: str, field: str, value: Any) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Set a field in hash.\n        \n        Creates the hash if it doesn't exist.\n        \n        Returns:\n            1\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            # Create new hash\n            new_dict = {field: value}\n            self._store[key] = (new_dict, self.HASH, None)\n            return 1\n        \n        value_store, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.HASH:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        value_store[field] = value\n        self._store[key] = (value_store, self.HASH, expiry)\n        return 1\n    \n    def hget(self, key: str, field: str) -> Any | None:\n        \"\"\"Return the field value.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Field value, or None if hash or field doesn't exist.\n        \n        Raises:\n            CommandError: On non-hash keys.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            return None\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.HASH:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        return value.get(field)\n    \n    def hdel(self, key: str, field: str) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Delete a field from hash.\n        \n        Returns:\n            1 if deleted, 0 if not found.\n        \n        Raises:\n            CommandError: On non-hash keys.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            return 0\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.HASH:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        if field in value:\n            del value[field]\n            self._store[key] = (value, self.HASH, expiry)\n            return 1\n        \n        return 0\n    \n    def hgetall(self, key: str) -> dict:\n        \"\"\"Return the internal dict object.\n        \n        If key doesn't exist, creates an empty hash first.\n        \n        Returns:\n            The dict object.\n        \n        Raises:\n            CommandError: On non-hash keys.\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            # Create empty hash\n            new_dict = {}\n            self._store[key] = (new_dict, self.HASH, None)\n            return new_dict\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        \n        if type_tag != self.HASH:\n            raise CommandError(f\"WRONGTYPE Operation against a key holding the wrong kind of value\")\n        \n        return value\n    \n    # ==================== Key Management ====================\n    \n    def expire(self, key: str, nseconds: int) -> None:\n        \"\"\"Set a timeout in seconds for a live key.\n        \n        Calling for a missing key is a no-op.\n        \n        Returns:\n            None\n        \"\"\"\n        entry = self._get_entry(key)\n        \n        if entry is None:\n            return None\n        \n        value, type_tag, expiry = entry\n        self._store[key] = (value, type_tag, time.time() + nseconds)\n        return None\n    \n    def kv_flush(self) -> int:\n        \"\"\"Remove all live keys and metadata.\n        \n        Returns:\n            Number of live keys removed.\n        \"\"\"\n        count = 0\n        now = time.time()\n        keys_to_delete = []\n        \n        for key, (value, type_tag, expiry) in self._store.items():\n            if expiry is None or expiry > now:\n                keys_to_delete.append(key)\n        \n        for key in keys_to_delete:\n            del self._store[key]\n            count += 1\n        \n        return count\n    \n    def save_to_disk(self, filename: str) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Persist the entire database state to a file using pickle.\n        \n        Returns:\n            True\n        \"\"\"\n        # Clean up expired keys before saving\n        now = time.time()\n        live_store = {}\n        for key, (value, type_tag, expiry) in self._store.items():\n            if expiry is None or expiry > now:\n                live_store[key] = (value, type_tag, expiry)\n        \n        with open(filename, 'wb') as f:\n            pickle.dump(live_store, f)\n        return True\n    \n    def restore_from_disk(self, filename: str) -> bool:\n        \"\"\"Restore database state from a pickle file.\n        \n        Returns:\n            True if restored, False if file doesn't exist.\n        \"\"\"\n        import os\n        if not os.path.exists(filename):\n            return False\n        \n        with open(filename, 'rb') as f:\n            self._store = pickle.load(f)\n        return True", "kind": "FileEditorObservation"}, "action_id": "8543e132-1121-4292-b126-363db49d9253", "kind": "ObservationEvent"}
